Remove phages and retrotransposons, and polydnaviruses

Since we are interested in insect viruses, let’s remove the phages https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacteriophage and retrotransposons

phage_families=read.table("../TABLES/phage_families.txt", h=FALSE)
# missing Herelleviridae
phage_families=phage_families$V1
phage_families=c(phage_families, "Herelleviridae", "Plectroviridae")
# retrotransposons + Polydnaviruses 
retro_transposons=c("Belpaoviridae", "Metaviridae", "Pseudoviridae", "Polydnaviridae")
phage_retrotransposons=c(phage_families,retro_transposons )

wga_cov2=wga_cov2[-which(wga_cov2$family %in% phage_retrotransposons),]

# further remove the contigs with no family assignation but having species name containing "phage"
if (length(grep("phage", wga_cov2$species))>0){
wga_cov2=wga_cov2[-grep("phage", wga_cov2$species),]
}

plot_heatmap=function(mymatrix=wga_cov2_viruses, pdf="test.pdf", name="coverage", colcex=3, rowcex=3, min=0.2, max=1, cluster_rows=TRUE, row_order=NA, cluster_cols=TRUE, col_order=NA, row_title="", show_heatmap_legend=TRUE, show_annotation_name=TRUE, colour_code_viruses=d){

  # dimension of the matrix
  ncols=dim(mymatrix)[2]
  
  # order rows according to something ?
if (cluster_rows){
  cluster_rows=TRUE
  print ("no special row order")
}
if (cluster_rows==FALSE){
  print ("Fixed row order")
  cluster_rows=FALSE
  mymatrix=mymatrix[row_order,]
}
  # extract virus taxonomy info
  taxo=mymatrix[, c((ncols-7):ncols)]

# define the form of names for viruses (rows)
mymatrix$pident=mymatrix$pident*100 #round the percent identity for blastx results
#mymatrix$identity[is.na(mymatrix$identity)]="~100" # to indicate that these are very similar to known viral genomic sequences
# define row labels
short_names=sub(pattern = "contig_", replacement = "c", rownames(mymatrix))
labels=paste(mymatrix$species, paste0(mymatrix$pident, "%"), mymatrix$seqs_length, short_names, sep=" ")

# order cols according to something ?
if (cluster_cols){
  cluster_cols=TRUE
  print ("no special cols order")
}
if (cluster_cols==FALSE){
  print ("Fixed cols order")
  cluster_cols=FALSE
  mymatrix=mymatrix[,col_order]
}


# define colour scheme
col_fun = colorRamp2(c(min, max), c("green", "red"))

# define annotation colors for cols
rows_annotation=strsplit(colnames(mymatrix)[1:(ncols-9)], split = "_", fixed = T)
rows_annotation=do.call(rbind.data.frame,rows_annotation)
names(rows_annotation)=c("species", "location", "year", "season", "libtype")
# to deal with the duplicated sample (D im taken as D. phalerat)
#rows_annotation$libtype[rows_annotation$species=="control"]="WGA"

if (sum(rows_annotation$libtype=="WGAbis")>0){
rows_annotation$libtype[rows_annotation$libtype=="WGAbis"]="WGA"
rows_annotation[rows_annotation$species=="H2O",]=c(NA, NA, NA, NA, "WGA")
}
if (sum(rows_annotation$libtype=="WTAbis")>0){
rows_annotation$libtype[rows_annotation$libtype=="WTAbis"]="WTA"
rows_annotation[rows_annotation$species=="H2O",]=c(NA, NA, NA, NA, "WTA")
}

colnames(mymatrix)[grepl("H2O",colnames(mymatrix))]="neg_control"

rows_annotation$season=as.factor(rows_annotation$season)
#levels(rows_annotation$season)=c(NA,"June", "Sept")
levels(rows_annotation$season)[levels(rows_annotation$season)=="Juin"]="June"
levels(rows_annotation$season)[levels(rows_annotation$season)=="Sept"]="Sept"
#levels(rows_annotation$season)[levels(rows_annotation$season)=="Sept"]="Sept"
#rows_annotation$season=factor(rows_annotation$season)
rows_annotation$year=factor(rows_annotation$year)
rows_annotation$location=factor(rows_annotation$location)
rows_annotation$species=factor(rows_annotation$species)
# reorder columns
rows_annotation=rows_annotation[,c(4,3,2,1)]

# define species colors
cols_ha=c(brewer.pal(3, "Set1"),brewer.pal(12, "Set3"))
